{{Orphan|date=March 2011}}
{{Infobox school | name = Montreal Oral School for the Deaf | image = | image_size = 300px | caption = | address = 4670 rue Sainte-Catherine Ouest | city = [[Westmount, Quebec|Westmount]] | province = [[Quebec]] | postcode = [[Postal codes in Canada|H3Z 1S5]] | country = Canada | coordinates = {{coord|45.47863|N|73.59587|W|region:CA-QC|display=inline,title}} | schooltype = Private School for the Deaf | founded = {{Start date|1950}}<ref name=CTV/> | grades_label = [[Education in Canada#Levels in education|Grades]] | grades = K-12 | enrollment = 160<ref name=CTV/> | enrollment_as_of = April 24, 2011 | language = [[English (language)|English]], [[French (language)|French]] | homepage = {{URL|http://www.montrealoralschool.com/}} }}
The '''Montreal Oral School for the Deaf''' (MOSD) is a provincial school in [[Westmount, Quebec]], [[Canada]] with programs serving [[Hearing impairment|deaf and hard-of-hearing]] students. The school was founded in 1950.<ref name=CTV>{{cite web |url= http://montreal.ctv.ca/servlet/an/local/CTVNews/20110423/mtl_deaf_110423/20110423/?hub=MontrealHome |title=CTV Montreal - School for the deaf marks 60 years|work=montreal.ctv.ca |date= 2011-04-23|accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref>
The school has a [[Early childhood education|preschool day program]], closed classrooms for [[elementary school]] children, and itinerant support for students of all ages mainstreamed into regular hearing classrooms.
The mission of the Montreal Oral School for the Deaf (MOSD) is to provide habilitation and education for children with hearing loss from infancy through to early adulthood.<ref>http://www.montrealoralschool.com/</ref>
